  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `./erigon --version`\r\n\r\n$ erigon --version\r\nerigon version 2.37.0-stable-12419c75\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\nErigon Command (with flags/config):\r\n\r\n erigon --version; rm -r /var/lib/erigon/*; /usr/bin/erigon --chain bor-mainnet --datadir /var/lib/erigon --db.pagesize 16kb --snapshots=false\r\n\r\nConcensus Layer:\r\n\r\nNethermind\r\n\r\nChain/Network: \r\n\r\nPolygon\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI'm trying to start erigon without snapshots.  Seems like it doesn't recognize the snapshot option.   \r\n$ erigon --version\r\nerigon version 2.37.0-stable-12419c75\r\n specifically \r\nINFO[01-29|19:29:38.015] Effective                                prune_flags= snapshot_flags=\"--snapshots=true\" history.v3=false\r\n\r\nversion 2.37.0: Broken\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26171839/215351833-262564fc-4d51-4807-8176-b76a8fb51114.png)\r\n\r\nversion 2.36.0: OK\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26171839/215351838-28c35f14-b3d9-4075-bab0-1ab980497481.png)\r\n",
